Gene Berg used to sell a kit of plastic parts that allowed one to  
measure the combustion chamber volume and thereby calculate the  
compression ratio.  At a local VW parts/repair place they used to  
sell a set of pistons for a Type 2 that had a dished out top.
On May 2, 2006, at 9:29 PM, Faster-Laster wrote:

> Here is something that is a bit different regarding these guys. I  
> have an engine in my 66 with about 80k trouble free miles. I  
> purchased this from aircooled.net a few years ago and have been  
> tickled pink with it. I know from experience with this engine and a  
> lot of here-say that it runs a low CR. As I am comtemplating what a  
> rebuild will perhaps entail I started to wonder if anyone has done  
> any real measuring on the internals. Specifically has anyone  
> checked the volume of the Combustion chamber, or happened to  
> measure a typical deck height. The general thought seems to be that  
> dished pistons are used in this motor, but can anyone confirm this?  
> From some searches on the web I could find nothing specific, other  
> than aircooled seems to offer a head upgrade (which if you guys  
> know the answers that would be great) and for obvious reasons have  
> at least seen what the stock setup seems to be.
